---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Thibaut LEFRANCOIS">
  <div
    class="max-w-prose text-base leading-relaxed text-neutral-500 flex flex-col gap-5 md:gap-6"
  >
    <p>
      This portfolio was published far too early, intentionally. I wanted a
      place to write, and Astro was the tool I'd chosen for both the blog and
      the portfolio, so I shipped what I had.
    </p>
    <p>
      The <a href="/blog" class="underline text-neutral-700">blog</a> is where I document
      what I learn along the way ; short experiments, discoveries, and the web rabbit
      holes that feed my
      <a href="/projects" class="underline text-neutral-700">project list</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Eventually, those projects will be showcased here in a more creative
      manner. For now, I'm still practicing to get there.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a
        href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1l69ztiHjXb1Q0WuAgiSPmeoh-eoq8Ep9/view?usp=sharing"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="underline text-neutral-700">View my CV &rarr;</a
      >
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2
    class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold mt-auto text-center sm:text-left"
  >
    &lt;full-stack and creative developer /&gt;
  </h2>
  <!--<p class="mt-auto text-xs text-neutral-400 animate-pulse">work in progress</p>-->
</BaseLayout>
